item.title: Rick Ross and his $280 000 Ferrari 458 Italia
item.description: Maybach Music Group’s customized Ferrari 458 Italia looks a little odd and crazy! The MMG, a record label owned by Rick Ross, decided to modify the Ferrari model. The end result was a gigantic 3-piece wheels 21-inch Ferrari painted with bright green and flat gray camouflage. The car’s nose was decorated with sharp shark-looking teeth on both sides. MMG presented the customized car in line with the release of its collaboration album Self Made 3 which came out in stores on September 17.

item.title: Who Has A Higher Net Worth: Joel Or Benji Madden?
item.description: Can you tell Joel and Benji Madden apart from each other? The twins are so identical, neither can we sometimes. All you really have to look for when telling them apart is the lady on each of their arms. If you see Cameron Diaz, odds are she's with her husband, Benji. If you see Nicole Richie, she's with Joel (it was actually Richie who introduced Benji to Diaz).

item.title: Who is Stephanie Mills dating? Stephanie Mills boyfriend, husband
item.description: Single Stephanie Mills  American Singer 60 Whois shedating right now? Stephanie Mills is currently single. RelationshipsStephanie Mills was previously married to Jeffrey Daniel (1980), Dino Meminger (1989) and Micheal Saunders (1993). Stephanie Mills has been in a relationship with Michael Jackson (1977 - 1980). AboutStephanie Mills is a 66 year old American Singer. Born Stephanie Dorthea Mills on 22nd March, 1957 in Bedford-Stuyvesant, Brooklyn, New York City, New York, USA, she is famous for her role as Dorothy in the Broadway production of The Wiz, and her hits like the Grammy Award winning song “Never Knew Love Like This Before” and her number one hit “Home” in a career that spans 1966–present and 1973–present and 1972–present.

item.title: 'An American Murder Mystery': Kathleen's Sister Talks Crime Scene
item.description: The death of Kathleen Peterson became national news in 2001 after her body was found in a pool of blood at the bottom of the staircase in the home she shared with husband Michael Peterson. Now, the Investigation Discovery network will air a new special titled An American Murder Mystery: The Staircase on Sunday, April 8, and will revisit the suspicious details of what really happened in the family’s home in Durham, North Carolina.

item.title: 6 'Love Island' Stars Who Made Millions After The Show
item.description: Quick LinksThe Couple Alex Bowman and Olivia Buckland Dani Dyer Amber Davies and Kem Cetinay Chris Hughes Olivia Atwood Molly Mae Hugh and Tom Fury Several famous Love Island stars have made millions after showing their charm on the show. Love Island is a reality show based on the theme of love and coupling. However, all the couples formed as part of this show are not necessarily romantic partners.

item.title: Construction begins on The Perch apartments in west Charlotte WSOC TV

Called The Perch, the two-building apartment project at 718 Gesco St. will be 217,000 square feet and have 213 studio, one-, two- and three-bedroom units with balconies and uptown views. The two met 13 years ago after Alina sent Caleb a message saying she wanted to practice her English. Back then, they were both 15 years old. Some years later, they lost touch but found each other again on Tinder.

item.title: Cameron Diaz Would Never Say Never to Returning to Acting
item.description: Returning to her roots? Cameron Diaz teased the possibility of her hitting the big screen in the distant future. “I feel really resolved. I mean, I never say never to anything, first of all,” the Bad Teacher star, 48, shared on Naomi Campbell’s YouTube series, No Filter With Naomi, on Tuesday, October 27. “But I feel really resolved. I haven’t made a movie since 2014. It’s been a long time, it’s been seven years or six years since I made a film.

item.title: CM Punks Lawyer Comments On AEW Termination
item.description: Stephen P. New, CM Punk‘s lawyer, comments on his AEW release. AEW terminated CM Punk’s contract on September 2 after he was involved in a backstage altercation with Jack Perry at AEW All In. The terms of Punk’s release were unclear, and fans buzzed about his future until he returned to WWE at WWE Survivor Series on November 25. Punk’s lawyer Stephen P. New appeared on the latest episode of Rumor & Innuendo with  Nick Hausman & Robert Karpeles.

item.title: Drake Loses $1 Million After Betting On World Cup
item.description: Drake is a betting man, but the odds weren’t in his favor during the World Cup. The rapper reportedly lost $1 million after betting that Argentina would win in the first 90 minutes.  Before the game, a video began circulating on social media showing Drake in a studio alongside a friend boasting about their bets. “I’ll take Argentina, he’ll take France. That will be a vibe,” he said.

item.title: Greg Olsen To Join Fox Sports As Commentator When NFL Career Ends
item.description: When Greg Olsen retires from football, the Pro Bowl tight end won't have to wait long to for a new career opportunity. According to a report from Andrew Marchand of the New York Post, Olsen will work alongside Fox Sports NFL play-by-play man Kevin Burkhardt as a commentator when his NFL career ends. Burkhardt and Olsen will serve as the No. 2 commentary team for Fox, behind Joe Buck and Pro Football Hall of Famer and three-time Super Bowl champion quarterback Troy Aikman.
